[00:00.41]	[Rome. The house of LEPIDUS.,]
[00:01.23]	[Enter DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS and LEPIDUS]
[00:02.05]LEPIDUS	Good Enobarbus, 'tis a worthy deed,
[00:04.71]	And shall become you well, to entreat your captain
[00:08.54]	To soft and gentle speech.
[00:10.73]DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS	I shall entreat him
[00:12.50]	To answer like himself: if Caesar move him,
[00:15.78]	Let Antony look over Caesar's head
[00:18.59]	And speak as loud as Mars. By Jupiter,
[00:21.53]	Were I the wearer of Antonius' beard,
[00:24.40]	I would not shave't to-day.
[00:26.65]LEPIDUS	'Tis not a time
[00:28.09]	For private stomaching.
[00:30.07]DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS	Every time
[00:31.23]	Serves for the matter that is then born in't.
[00:34.72]LEPIDUS	But small to greater matters must give way.
[00:38.07]DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS	Not if the small come first.
[00:40.39]LEPIDUS	Your speech is passion:
[00:42.37]	But, pray you, stir no embers up. Here comes
[00:45.66]	The noble Antony.
[00:47.23]	[Enter MARK ANTONY and VENTIDIUS]
[00:48.05]DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS	And yonder, Caesar.
[00:49.69]	[Enter OCTAVIUS CAESAR, MECAENAS, and AGRIPPA]
[00:50.51]MARK ANTONY	If we compose well here, to Parthia:
[00:53.31]	Hark, Ventidius.
[00:54.75]OCTAVIUS CAESAR	I do not know,
[00:56.11]	Mecaenas; ask Agrippa.
[00:57.96]LEPIDUS	Noble friends,
[00:59.33]	That which combined us was most great, and let not
[01:03.15]	A leaner action rend us. What's amiss,
[01:06.09]	May it be gently heard: when we debate
[01:09.10]	Our trivial difference loud, we do commit
[01:12.31]	Murder in healing wounds: then, noble partners,
[01:15.80]	The rather, for I earnestly beseech,
[01:18.60]	Touch you the sourest points with sweetest terms,
[01:22.36]	Nor curstness grow to the matter.
[01:25.03]MARK ANTONY	'Tis spoken well.
[01:26.53]	Were we before our armies, and to fight.
[01:29.61]	I should do thus.
[01:31.18]	[Flourish]
[01:32.00]OCTAVIUS CAESAR	Welcome to Rome.
[01:33.50]MARK ANTONY	Thank you.
[01:34.60]OCTAVIUS CAESAR	Sit.
[01:35.28]MARK ANTONY	Sit, sir.
[01:36.24]OCTAVIUS CAESAR	Nay, then.
[01:37.26]MARK ANTONY	I learn, you take things ill which are not so,
[01:40.75]	Or being, concern you not.
[01:42.87]OCTAVIUS CAESAR	I must be laugh'd at,
[01:44.71]	If, or for nothing or a little, I
[01:47.31]	Should say myself offended, and with you
[01:50.46]	Chiefly i' the world; more laugh'd at, that I should
[01:54.28]	Once name you derogately, when to sound your name
[01:58.04]	It not concern'd me.
[01:59.82]MARK ANTONY	My being in Egypt, Caesar,
[02:01.94]	What was't to you?
[02:03.58]OCTAVIUS CAESAR	No more than my residing here at Rome
[02:06.59]	Might be to you in Egypt: yet, if you there
[02:09.87]	Did practise on my state, your being in Egypt
[02:13.35]	Might be my question.
[02:15.20]MARK ANTONY	How intend you, practised?
[02:17.32]OCTAVIUS CAESAR	You may be pleased to catch at mine intent
[02:20.67]	By what did here befal me. Your wife and brother
[02:24.36]	Made wars upon me; and their contestation
[02:27.57]	Was theme for you, you were the word of war.
[02:30.92]MARK ANTONY	You do mistake your business; my brother never
[02:34.48]	Did urge me in his act: I did inquire it;
[02:37.62]	And have my learning from some true reports,
[02:41.04]	That drew their swords with you. Did he not rather
[02:44.87]	Discredit my authority with yours;
[02:47.60]	And make the wars alike against my stomach,
[02:50.95]	Having alike your cause? Of this my letters
[02:54.30]	Before did satisfy you. If you'll patch a quarrel,
[02:58.06]	As matter whole you have not to make it with,
[03:01.54]	It must not be with this.
[03:03.66]OCTAVIUS CAESAR	You praise yourself
[03:05.44]	By laying defects of judgment to me; but
[03:08.58]	You patch'd up your excuses.
[03:10.91]MARK ANTONY	Not so, not so;
[03:12.28]	I know you could not lack, I am certain on't,
[03:15.69]	Very necessity of this thought, that I,
[03:18.70]	Your partner in the cause 'gainst which he fought,
[03:22.46]	Could not with graceful eyes attend those wars
[03:26.08]	Which fronted mine own peace. As for my wife,
[03:29.50]	I would you had her spirit in such another:
[03:32.85]	The third o' the world is yours; which with a snaffle
[03:36.81]	You may pace easy, but not such a wife.
[03:39.82]DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS	Would we had all such wives, that the men might go
[03:43.65]	to wars with the women!
[03:45.63]MARK ANTONY	So much uncurbable, her garboils, Caesar
[03:48.71]	Made out of her impatience, which not wanted
[03:52.13]	Shrewdness of policy too, I grieving grant
[03:55.41]	Did you too much disquiet: for that you must
[03:58.82]	But say, I could not help it.
