[04:02.58]	When rioting in Alexandria; you
[04:05.11]	Did pocket up my letters, and with taunts
[04:08.33]	Did gibe my missive out of audience.
[04:11.20]MARK ANTONY	Sir,
[04:11.88]	He fell upon me ere admitted: then
[04:14.61]	Three kings I had newly feasted, and did want
[04:18.10]	Of what I was i' the morning: but next day
[04:21.31]	I told him of myself; which was as much
[04:24.39]	As to have ask'd him pardon. Let this fellow
[04:27.81]	Be nothing of our strife; if we contend,
[04:30.88]	Out of our question wipe him.
[04:33.28]OCTAVIUS CAESAR	You have broken
[04:34.78]	The article of your oath; which you shall never
[04:38.40]	Have tongue to charge me with.
[04:40.86]LEPIDUS	Soft, Caesar!
[04:42.09]MARK ANTONY	No,
[04:42.71]	Lepidus, let him speak:
[04:44.62]	The honour is sacred which he talks on now,
[04:47.97]	Supposing that I lack'd it. But, on, Caesar;
[04:51.18]	The article of my oath.
[04:53.17]OCTAVIUS CAESAR	To lend me arms and aid when I required them;
[04:56.65]	The which you both denied.
[04:58.84]MARK ANTONY	Neglected, rather;
[05:00.41]	And then when poison'd hours had bound me up
[05:03.90]	From mine own knowledge. As nearly as I may,
[05:07.25]	I'll play the penitent to you: but mine honesty
[05:10.87]	Shall not make poor my greatness, nor my power
[05:14.42]	Work without it. Truth is, that Fulvia,
[05:17.36]	To have me out of Egypt, made wars here;
[05:20.44]	For which myself, the ignorant motive, do
[05:23.58]	So far ask pardon as befits mine honour
[05:26.73]	To stoop in such a case.
[05:28.78]LEPIDUS	'Tis noble spoken.
[05:30.35]MECAENAS	If it might please you, to enforce no further
[05:33.84]	The griefs between ye: to forget them quite
[05:37.19]	Were to remember that the present need
[05:40.26]	Speaks to atone you.
[05:42.04]LEPIDUS	Worthily spoken, Mecaenas.
[05:44.16]DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS	Or, if you borrow one another's love for the
[05:47.58]	instant, you may, when you hear no more words of
[05:51.20]	Pompey, return it again: you shall have time to
[05:54.75]	wrangle in when you have nothing else to do.
[05:58.17]MARK ANTONY	Thou art a soldier only: speak no more.
[06:01.18]DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS	That truth should be silent I had almost forgot.
[06:04.87]MARK ANTONY	You wrong this presence; therefore speak no more.
[06:08.56]DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS	Go to, then; your considerate stone.
[06:11.30]OCTAVIUS CAESAR	I do not much dislike the matter, but
[06:14.23]	The manner of his speech; for't cannot be
[06:17.45]	We shall remain in friendship, our conditions
[06:20.93]	So differing in their acts. Yet if I knew
[06:24.15]	What hoop should hold us stanch, from edge to edge
[06:27.97]	O' the world I would pursue it.
[06:30.43]AGRIPPA	Give me leave, Caesar,--
[06:32.28]OCTAVIUS CAESAR	Speak, Agrippa.
[06:33.65]AGRIPPA	Thou hast a sister by the mother's side,
[06:36.79]	Admired Octavia: great Mark Antony
[06:39.53]	Is now a widower.
